      Description "BCBSKCCommon Drug Claim Extract job"
      NextID "154"
      Container "V0"
      FullDescription =+=+=+=
COPYRIGHT 2010 BLUE CROSS/BLUE SHIELD OF KANSAS CITY 


CALLED BY : BCBSKCCommDrugClmExtrLoadSeq

DESCRIPTION:  
   
 Reads the Medtrak drug file from the extract program and adds business rules and reformats to the drug claim common format. Then runs shared container DrugClmPkey
    

MODIFICATIONS:
Developer                                        Date                       Change Description                                                   Project #             Development Project          Code Reviewer               Date Reviewed  
=======================================================================================================================================================================
Kaushik Kapoor                                2018-01-17             Initial Programming                                                    5828                    IntegrateDev2                     Kalyan Neelam               2018-02-26 

Saikiran Subbagari                        2019-01-15           Added the TXNMY_CD column                                      5887                    IntegrateDev1
                                                                                                    in DrugClmPK Container      

Bhargava Rampilla                        2019-10-16              Modified feilds as per the 
                                                                             OptumRX transformation rules:                                              6131                    Integrate Dev1
                                                                                                  GNRC_DRUG_IN
                                                                                                  MAIL_ORDER_IN (Lkup added)
                                                                                                  MAC_REDC_IN
                                                                                                  NON_FRMLRY_DRUG_IN
                                                                                                  RECON_DT_SK
                                                                                                  INGR_SAV_AMT
                                                                                                  MBR_DIFF_PD_AMT
